-- Auburn, Oregon to Play for College Football Title; TCU Heads to Rose Bowl
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2010-12-06T01:42:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-06/auburn-oregon-to-play-for-college-football-title-tcu-heads-to-rose-bowl.html
Auburn
University and the University of Oregon will meet in college
football’s championship game after finishing atop the Bowl
Championship Series standings.   Auburn (13-0) will face Oregon (12-0) in the BCS title game
on Jan. 10 in Glendale, Arizona.   Texas Christian University (12-0) finished third in the BCS
rankings and will play the University of Wisconsin (11-1) in the
Rose Bowl on Jan. 1. Also on New Year’s Day, the University of
Oklahoma (10-2) meets the University of Connecticut (8-4) in the
Fiesta Bowl.  In other BCS games, Stanford University (11-1) and Virginia
Tech (11-2) play in the Orange Bowl on Jan. 3, while Ohio State
(11-1) faces the University of Arkansas (10-2) in the Sugar Bowl
on Jan. 4.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  